ears.\n*   **² AWS Footnote:** Includes property and equipment added under finance leases of $117 million, $238 million, and $1.9 billion in 2023, 2024, and 2025, respectively. Build-to-suit lease arrangements were $1 million, $8 million, and $421 million for those same years.\n*   **Geographic Concentration:** The vast majority of Amazon's physical assets are concentrated in the U.S. U.S. property and equipment, net, and operating leases were $196.0 billion, $241.6 billion, and $321.9 billion as of year-end 2023, 2024, and 2025. Non-U.S. assets were $80.7 billion, $87.2 billion, and $121.2 billion. No single non-U.S. country accounted for more than 10% of the consolidated total.",
